<br>
Yes there are things that I think are obviously exploits. Common sense dictates that. However the operative phrase there is 'I THINK' - what I think is not necessarily what others would think. I thinhk, to repeat the example, and the dupping of Fv keys is a joke and defeats the whole ideas of keys and is thus an exploit - Sony has proclaimed this not so - I clearly thought wrongly in this case.<br>
<br>
Clearly there are also encounters where things are working correctly. (I root mob, I snare mob, I nuke mob, root breaks, I run, re-nuke etc etc)<br>
<br>
There is an incredibly huge area in between what (in my own opinion) are obvious exploits and what are (again in my opinion) clearly not - it is here that the debate lies and it is here I posit that we cannot judge.<br>
<br>
However when push comes to shove whether something is an exploit or not comes down to what GM_09 decides on the day it forst comes to his/her/it's attention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dracomin>Dracomin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/03 12:25:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25564.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Define &quot;exploit&quot;</span><hr size=1> There are times when you outright know something is an exploit and should not be used.  If you are caught doing it, you probably will get in trouble with GM and could get an account warning.<br>
<br>
There are times when its not black and white though.  Let me give you an example.  CoH does NOT work in alot of places within the Elemental Planes.  It can be perceived that it was VI's intentions that noone is able to take shortcuts to those places at all.  If you get home a bit late, too bad.  Some guilds however have found a way around that.  Have rogue with Shroud of Stealth be translocated to zi.  Kill the person who needs coh and get consent.  Then drag corpse while using Hide and Sneak to get past mobs.  Bring corpse to raid and cleric rezzes corpse.  Boom...ghetto CoH completed.<br>
<br>
Now its not obvious on whether this was intended or not.  But if a GM or guide is in zone, it would be best to quit doing this.  Dual message inside an elemental plane would certainly get some attention from a GM that is already there.  What you dont know is how the GM thinks.  Its possible that 9 GMs out of 10 would not mind it at all, but that 10th one would consider that an exploit and would take action.  To be on the safe side you just dont do it while GM is around.<br>
<br>
