<br>
Usually after they witnessed this action, the confronted the player, and based on the conversation they did a comprehensive chat log review.<br>
<br>
From there they did a boolean query looking for things that mentioned SeQ outright, or phrases commonly used in referring to SeQ abilities, in addition to searching for the redflags that could be sent up that gave away its presence such as zoning, speed, and radar.<br>
<br>
Then after all that they usually guessed, because without breaking the law they still didnt have 100% proof against anyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nulrec>Nulrec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/03 9:47:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25564.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Exploit</span><hr size=1> Exploit = what hte US is doing in Iraq.<br>
